CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Prince George’s County – Expanding Access to Early Childhood Education and
3 Child Care
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the State Department of Education Prince George’s County
5 government to develop an implementation and financing plan to expand access to
6 high–quality early childhood education and child care in Prince George’s County for
7 children from birth through 3 years; requiring the Department county government
8 to consult with certain entities; requiring the plan to include certain analyses; and
9 generally relating to early childhood education and child care in Prince George’s
10 County.
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That:
13 (a) The State Department of Education Prince George’s County government shall
14 develop an implementation and financing plan to expand access to high–quality early
15 childhood education and child care in Prince George’s County for children from birth
16 through 3 years.
17 (b) To complete the plan, the Department Prince George’s County government
18 shall consult with the Prince George’s County Public School System, the Prince George’s
19 County Council, the State Department of Education, businesses, and relevant State
20 agencies organizations.
21 (c) The plan shall include an analysis of:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
