2 SENATE BILL 672
1 (1) the cost to parents, the county, and the State;
2 (2) the workforce needs of early childhood education and child care
3 providers to expand access;
4 (3) the capacity of early childhood education and child care providers to
5 serve more children; and
6 (4) additional county and State revenue options to expand access.
7 (d) On or before December 1, 2026 2027, the Department county government shall
8 submit the plan to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government
9 Article, the General Assembly and the members of the Prince George’s County Delegation
10 to the General Assembly.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2026.
